Empty line before the end of the section, for readability. Same thing below.

wrapping a namespace in a section with no extra bits in between, *especially* when they have the same name is just confusing.
```suggestion
```

My reasoning was that sections can be collapsed in VS Code, making it easier to see at a glance what's in the file. However, namespaces have the same effect, so I'm convinced. Changed (here and elsewhere).

```suggestion
namespace PartialHomeomorph

/- post-compose with a partial homeomorphism -/
```
